{"info": {"author": "Mohammed Shaawa", "author_email": "mshaawa963@gmail.com", "bugtrack_url": null, "classifiers": ["License :: OSI Approved :: MIT License", "Operating System :: OS Independent", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3"], "description": "# PyIslam\n\nPyIslam is a python library that provide easier way to get verses and soon hadith.\n\nThis Package uses https://Quran.com api to retrieve verses and some info\n\n# Examples\n\n## Quran\n\n* Get a random verse from quran\n\n```python\nfrom pyislam import Quran\n\nQ = Quran()\nprint(Q.get_random_verse)\n```\n* Get a specific verse\n```python\nfrom pyislam import Quran\n\nQ = Quran(chapter = 5, verse = 10)\nprint(Q.Verse) # Case Sensitive\n```\n\n`Q.Verse` will return a dict in this structure : `{'ar' : '<Arabic Verse>', 'en' : '<English Translation>', 'verse_number' : <Verse Number>, 'chapter_id' : <Chapter ID>`\n\n### Tafsir\nComing soon\n\n## Hadith\nComing Soon\n\n# Installing\n  `pip install pyislam`\n\n\n", "description_content_type": "text/markdown", "docs_url": null, "download_url": "", "downloads": {"last_day": -1, "last_month": -1, "last_week": -1}, "home_page": "https://github.com/moha369/pyislam", "keywords": "islam quran sunnah", "license": "MIT", "maintainer": "", "maintainer_email": "", "name": "pyislam", "package_url": "https://pypi.org/project/pyislam/", "platform": "", "project_url": "https://pypi.org/project/pyislam/", "project_urls": {"Homepage": "https://github.com/moha369/pyislam"}, "release_url": "https://pypi.org/project/pyislam/0.1.1/", "requires_dist": ["requests"], "requires_python": ">=3.6", "summary": "An Islamic Python Package", "version": "0.1.1", "yanked": false, "html_description": "<div class=\"project-description\">\n            <h1>PyIslam</h1>\n<p>PyIslam is a python library that provide easier way to get verses and soon hadith.</p>\n<p>This Package uses <a href=\"https://Quran.com\" rel=\"nofollow\">https://Quran.com</a> api to retrieve verses and some info</p>\n<h1>Examples</h1>\n<h2>Quran</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Get a random verse from quran</li>\n</ul>\n<pre><span class=\"kn\">from</span> <span class=\"nn\">pyislam</span> <span class=\"kn\">import</span> <span class=\"n\">Quran</span>\n\n<span class=\"n\">Q</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"n\">Quran</span><span class=\"p\">()</span>\n<span class=\"nb\">print</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">Q</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">get_random_verse</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n</pre>\n<ul>\n<li>Get a specific verse</li>\n</ul>\n<pre><span class=\"kn\">from</span> <span class=\"nn\">pyislam</span> <span class=\"kn\">import</span> <span class=\"n\">Quran</span>\n\n<span class=\"n\">Q</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"n\">Quran</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">chapter</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"mi\">5</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"n\">verse</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"mi\">10</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n<span class=\"nb\">print</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">Q</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">Verse</span><span class=\"p\">)</span> <span class=\"c1\"># Case Sensitive</span>\n</pre>\n<p><code>Q.Verse</code> will return a dict in this structure : <code>{'ar' : '&lt;Arabic Verse&gt;', 'en' : '&lt;English Translation&gt;', 'verse_number' : &lt;Verse Number&gt;, 'chapter_id' : &lt;Chapter ID&gt;</code></p>\n<h3>Tafsir</h3>\n<p>Coming soon</p>\n<h2>Hadith</h2>\n<p>Coming Soon</p>\n<h1>Installing</h1>\n<p><code>pip install pyislam</code></p>\n\n          </div>"}, "last_serial": 5968037, "releases": {"0.1": [{"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "24fb9b921df93d25a5238774cf7f9ba1", "sha256": "045a67053dee3da8594ef72aa284cc6c44f8e3bb7eaa0f3b10c22b16346f3103"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "pyislam-0.1-py3-none-any.whl", "has_sig": false, "md5_digest": "24fb9b921df93d25a5238774cf7f9ba1", "packagetype": "bdist_wheel", "pytho